{
  "texts": [
    "The algorithmic initialization protocol, as shown in Extended Data Fig. 3a, proceeds as follows: 1.",
    "Enter (m + 1, n + 1) to create two unpaired spins in the double-dot system. 2.",
    "This results in one of the |↓↓⟩, |↓↑⟩, |↑↓⟩ and |↑↑⟩ states.",
    "The probability of creating the ground state |↓↓⟩ decreases as the temperature increases, as the thermal energy becomes comparable or greater than the qubit exchange coupling and the Zeeman energies. 3.",
    "Ramp to the PSB region for parity readout and apply a filter that rejects odd-parity states."
  ]
}